<br>
The figure above are for space power reactors. For propulsion systems, a scale up is required.<br>
<br>
A VASIMR uses something like a 10 mw reactor under continous power for months out and months back.<br>
<br>
Using our crude scaling, the VASIMR will reach equilibrium at 60 million curies fission products.<br>
<br>
A nuclear rocket, such as a NERVA, has a shorter burn, but more intense power output. The NERVA Phoebus was rated at 5,000 megawatts, but was tested only at 4,000 megawatts. Again, when I get some time, I will do some figuring.<br>
